The global medical waste management market is segmented based on type, treatment site, and service. In terms of type, the market is categorized into hazardous and non-hazardous waste. The hazardous waste segment is expected to dominate the market due to the strict regulations surrounding the disposal of medical waste that poses a risk to human health or the environment. Non-hazardous waste management is also significant, encompassing waste that does not pose a threat like regular trash but still requires proper disposal. Treatment site segmentation includes onsite and offsite management. Onsite management is preferred for its convenience and immediacy in dealing with waste at healthcare facilities, while offsite management involves transportation to specialized treatment or disposal facilities. The service segment comprises collection, transportation, and storage services; treatment and disposal services; and recycling services. The treatment and disposal services segment is anticipated to witness substantial growth owing to the rising emphasis on environmentally friendly waste management practices.

